modules.description: This module supports parsing ISO 8601 date, time, and datetime values from strings or lexbuf inputs into float-based timestamps, with optional timezone handling, and converts them back to standardized string representations. It operates on float values for naive timestamps and float pairs for timezone-aware datetime values, offering both basic/extended formatting variants and customizable output through OCaml's `Format` module. It is useful for processing inconsistently formatted timestamps in logs, converting legacy time data to numeric representations, or generating ISO 8601 strings for data interchange.

This module parses and prints ISO 8601 and RFC 3339 date, time, and datetime values, supporting both basic and extended format variants. It handles naive timestamps as floats and timezone-aware datetimes as float pairs, with optional timezone conversion and customizable output via the `Format` module. Use it to process loosely formatted timestamps from logs, convert legacy time data to numeric form, or generate standardized datetime strings for data serialization or API responses.
